      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "They returned from the sepulchre — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To Jerusalem; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and told all these things to the eleven ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Apostles, in the course, probably, of that morning, for it is not likely that they found them all collected together in one body; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and to all the rest ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Namely, at different times. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And their words seemed to them as idle tales, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — Their Master’s crucifixion had given such a severe blow to their faith, that they had laid aside all the thoughts which they had entertained of his being the Messiah. And, therefore, they had not the least expectation of his resurrection, notwithstanding he had often predicted it to them: nay, they looked upon the story which the women told them about it as a mere chimera, the delusion of a disordered imagination. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Then arose Peter, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — Or rather, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "But Peter, arising; ran to the sepulchre ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— That is, Peter was an exception: the tidings brought by Mary Magdalene, and the other women, did not seem ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "as idle tales ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to him, nor to John, who now arose and went with him, and got to the sepulchre before him. See on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 20:1-10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
