            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", who repeateth this piece of history more largely than the rest. It is plain that scarce any of the disciples gave credit to the first relation of the women; but yet, it being near the city, Peter and John thought it worth the while to go and see. For though Peter alone be mentioned here, yet John is mentioned, ",
        "children": []
